# Deployment & environment (ALECO PIS)

## Always verify

- Edits must work **locally** (typical: `VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000`) **and** when the SPA is built for **production** (`VITE_API_URL` = public **HTTPS** API origin). Browsers cannot use your machine’s `localhost` for real users.
- Treat **Vercel** (SPA) and **Render** (API) as **examples**. Do not add code that only works on those hostnames unless guarded by env.

## Use these patterns

- **API base URL:** `getApiBaseUrl()` / `apiUrl()` from `src/config/apiBase.js` and `src/utils/api.js`. Axios: `src/api/axiosConfig.js`.
- **Never** hardcode production API or SPA URLs in `src/` or route handlers—use `import.meta.env.VITE_*` (frontend) or `process.env.*` (backend).
- **Remember:** `VITE_*` is **inlined at build time**. Changing it requires a **new frontend deploy**.

## Backend (Express)

- **CORS:** `backend/config/corsOrigins.js` — localhost defaults for dev + `PUBLIC_APP_URL`, `FRONTEND_ORIGIN`, `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS` for deployed SPA origins (no vendor URL baked in). Production API should set at least one of those env vars; `server.js` may log a warning if `NODE_ENV=production` and none are set.
- **Production SPA build:** `getApiBaseUrl()` throws if neither `VITE_API_URL` nor `VITE_API_URL_PRODUCTION` is set—do not ship a prod bundle without them.

## Before finishing a task

- [ ] No new hardcoded `https://…vercel.app` / `…onrender.com` in app logic.
- [ ] New `fetch`/axios calls use shared helpers or env-based base URL.

**Full detail:** `docs/ENV_AND_DEPLOYMENT_PRINCIPLES.md`
